</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>AB2528:v98#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="AB2528"/><meta name="dc:title" content="AB &#xA;              2528-&#xA;                AMENDED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td align="center"><span style=" text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 1em">
                Amended
               IN </span><span style=" text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 1em">
                Senate
              </span> <span style="text-transform: uppercase">June 22, 2026</span><br/></td></tr></tbody><tbody><tr><td align="center"/></tr></tbody></table></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><font size="3" style="FONT-FAMILY: MinionPC, Arial Unicode MS">
                    CALIFORNIA LEGISLATURE—
                    2025–2026 REGULAR SESSION</font></div><br clear="all"/><span id="bill_house_num"><div style="float: left; width:50%; font-weight: bold; "><span style="text-transform: uppercase; text-align:left;width:50%;"><b>
                Assembly Bill
              </b></span></div><div style="float:right; width:50%; text-align:right;"><span style="text-transform: uppercase;"><b>No. 2528</b></span></div></span><hr/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td id="bill_authors" align="center"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Introduced by Assembly Member Solache<br/></span></td></tr><tr><td id="bill_intro_date" align="center" class="textcenter"><br/>February 20, 2026</td></tr></tbody></table></div><hr/><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> An act to amend Section 72024 of the Education Code, relating to community colleges. </span></div><br clear="all"/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">AB 2528, as amended, Solache.
                          Community colleges: governing board member compensation.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Existing law establishes the California Community Colleges, administered by the Board of Governors of the California Community Colleges, as one of the segments of public postsecondary education in the state. Existing law establishes community college districts throughout the state under the administration of community college district governing boards. Existing law requires the governing board of each community college district to establish, maintain, operate, and govern one or more community colleges, as provided. Existing law authorizes the compensation of<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> governing</i></font> board members that actually attend all meetings held by the governing board, not to exceed a specified amount from $120 to $1,500, inclusive, based on the number of full-time equivalent students in the community
			 college district, as provided. </div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This bill would increase the authorized compensation for community college<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> district</i></font> governing board members that<font color="#B30000"><strike> actually</strike></font> attend all meetings held by the governing board, not to exceed a specified amount from $600 to $4,500, inclusive, based on the number of full-time equivalent students in the community college district, as provided.<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> The bill would require the governing board to provide public notice at least 30 days before a public meeting at which the governing board proposes to increase the compensation of the governing board members, as provided.</i></font></div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="vote">
      Vote:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">MAJORITY</span>  </span><span id="appropriation">
      Appropriation:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span><span id="localprogram">
      Local Program:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><div id="bill"><div style=" text-transform: uppercase"><h2 style=" text-align: left;">The people of the State of California do enact as follows:</h2><br/></div><div id="s10.2167821410763422"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0" class="ActionLine"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;">SECTION 1.</h3> Section 72024 of the Education Code is amended to read:</div><div><div id="id_AB152F43-AC95-41AA-9350-E517D3E9BE78"><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;">72024.</h6> (a) (1) In<font color="#B30000"><strike> any</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> a</i></font> community college district that is not located in a city and county, and in which the full-time equivalent students (FTES) for the prior college year exceeded 60,000, the governing board may prescribe, as compensation for the services of each member of the<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> governing</i></font> board<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> of a community college district</i></font> who<font color="#B30000"><strike> actually</strike></font>
						attends all meetings held by the<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> governing</i></font> board, a sum not to exceed four thousand five hundred dollars ($4,500) in any month.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) In<font color="#B30000"><strike> any</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> a</i></font> community college district in which the FTES for the prior college year was 60,000 or less, but more than 25,000, each member of the governing board of the<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> community college</i></font> district who<font color="#B30000"><strike> actually</strike></font> attends all meetings held by the<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>
						governing</i></font> board may receive as compensation for the member’s service a sum not to exceed three thousand dollars ($3,000) in any month.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(3) In<font color="#B30000"><strike> any</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> a</i></font> community college district in which the FTES for the prior college year was 25,000 or less, but more than 10,000, each member of the governing board of the<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> community college</i></font>
						district who<font color="#B30000"><strike> actually</strike></font> attends all meetings held<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> by the governing board</i></font> may receive as compensation for  the member’s service a sum not to exceed two thousand dollars ($2,000) in any month.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(4) In<font color="#B30000"><strike> any</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> a</i></font> community college district in which the FTES for the prior college year was 10,000 or less, but more than 1,000, each member of the governing board of the<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> community college</i></font> district who<font color="#B30000"><strike> actually</strike></font>
						attends all meetings held by the<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> governing</i></font> board may receive as compensation for the member’s service a sum not to exceed
						one thousand two hundred dollars ($1,200) in any month.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(5) In<font color="#B30000"><strike> any</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> a</i></font> community college district in which the FTES for the prior college year was 1,000 or less, but more than 150, each member of the governing board of the<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> community college</i></font> district who<font color="#B30000"><strike> actually</strike></font> attends all meetings held by the<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> governing</i></font> board may receive as compensation for the member’s service a sum not to exceed six
						hundred dollars ($600) in any month.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(b) <font color="#B30000"><strike>Any </strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>A </i></font>member of a governing board<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> of a community college district</i></font> who does not attend all meetings held by the<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> governing</i></font> board in any month may receive, as compensation for the member’s service, an amount not greater than a pro rata share of the number of meetings<font color="#B30000"><strike> actually</strike></font> attended based upon the maximum compensation authorized by this section.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(c) The compensation of members of the governing board of a community college district newly organized or reorganized shall be governed by subdivision (a). For this purpose, the total FTES in all of the community colleges of the<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> community college</i></font> district in the college year that the organization or reorganization became effective shall be deemed to be the FTES in the<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> community college</i></font> district for the prior college year.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(d) A member<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> of the governing board of a community college district</i></font> may be paid for
						any meeting when absent if the<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> governing</i></font> board, by resolution duly adopted and included in its minutes, finds that, at the time of the meeting, the member is performing services outside the meeting for the community college district, the member was ill or on jury duty, or the member’s absence was due to a hardship deemed acceptable by the<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> governing</i></font> board. The compensation shall be a charge against the funds of the<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> community college</i></font> district.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(e) On an annual basis, the governing board<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> of a
						community college district</i></font> may increase the compensation of individual<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> governing</i></font> board members beyond the limits delineated in this section, in an amount not to exceed 5 percent based on the present monthly rate of compensation.<font color="#B30000"><strike> Any</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> An</i></font> increase made pursuant to this section shall be effective upon approval by the governing<font color="#B30000"><strike> board.</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> board of the community college district.</i></font>
						The action may be rejected by a majority of the voters in that<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> community college</i></font> district voting in a referendum established for that purpose, as prescribed by Chapter 2 (commencing with Section 9100) of Division 9 of the Elections Code.</div><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(f) (1) A governing board of a community college district shall provide public notice at least 30 days before a public meeting at which the governing board proposes to increase the compensation for the services of each member of the governing board pursuant to subdivisions (a) and (e).</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) The public notice shall be posted on the home page of the internet website of the community college district
						and shall be accessible through a prominent direct link.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(3) The public notice shall include all of the following information:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(A) The current dollar amount of compensation for members of the governing board who attend all meetings held by the governing board.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(B) The proposed new dollar amount of compensation for members of the governing board who attend all meetings held by the governing board.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(C) The date, time, and location of the public meeting at which the proposed increase in governing board member compensation will be considered.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(4) The public notice shall be provided directly to the exclusive representative or representatives of all bargaining units of the community college
						district.</div></i></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(g) (1) It is the intent of the Legislature to encourage a governing board of a community college district to consider, at the time that the governing board considers increasing governing board member compensation, providing compensation to student members of the governing board in an amount to be determined by the governing board, not to exceed the compensation received by other governing board members.</div></i></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) It is the further intent of the Legislature that compensation provided to a student member of the governing board while fulfilling their duties not count towards meeting the maximum household income and asset levels, as described in
						subdivision (k) of Section 69432.7, for purposes of determining the student member’s eligibility for student financial aid. </div></i></font></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></body></html>
